                <p><bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr1997"/>, pp. 33-34 n. <citedRange>3 A</citedRange></bibl> 
                    (cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>1999.623</citedRange></bibl>), whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2179, A</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>086000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀριστοτέλης">Ἀριστοτέλης</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Βασιλοκρέων" type="patronymic">Βασιλοκρέοντος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Aristotélès fils de Basilokréôn.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Aristoteles son of Basilokreon.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Aristoteles figlio di Basilokreon.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Found in the same tomb as <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr086100</ref>; although there is no common element in the onomastics, both deceased were probably of the same family.</p>
             <p>About the tomb of provenance see commentary at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGcyr086100</ref>.</p>
	           <p>About the name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Βασιλοκρέων</foreign>, see <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>1999.623</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
